originalText.text: An extremely shady and dishonest company. I was planning an out of state Bachelor party and made a poor decision of trusting the owner of this company (Stevi) and all the assurances she gave me over email and phone about the quality of her automobiles. To make a long story short, I wound up paying over $1,300 for a limo she promised us is an "awesome car"; It showed up in 90 degree heat with absolute ZERO, 100% BROKEN Air Conditioning, and a broken audio system. Are you freaking kidding me? Dripping sweat from the second we left for dinner to the moment we returned home. When I reached out to the owner following the rental, absolutely no response. In addition, I got ripped off for an additional $160 because they pre-charge you for tip and do not make that clear. What kind of disrespectful human being does this, then stonewalls the customer? I'm posting this in hopes others will think twice and not run the risk of ruining their special occasion by working with someone who has zero heart. She doesnt invest in her fleet, the cars old and beaten up. If you must, see and evaluate the car in person. Test the radio connection. Test the AC. Do NOT allow them to pre-charge you a tip before you have the opportunity to experience their "service." Thanks, Stevi.
